model.name: Karlstaedt2019 - G6P accumulation via Phosphoglucose isomerase inhibition in heart muscles

body.p: This model is described in the article:

p.b: Glucose 6-phosphate accumulates via phosphoglucose isomerase inhibition in heart muscle.

body.p: Karlstaedt, A and Khanna, R and Thangam, M and Taegtmeyer, H Circulation Research (2019)
The model describes glycolysis (including pyruvate oxidation and ATP turnover) in cardiomyocytes. An extension of the same model includes the pentose phosphate pathway.
